<topic id="Sample Page">
  <title>Resource Identifier</title>
  <p>The resource identifier is expressed by a URI with the following
format:</p>
  <p>&lt;scheme&gt;://&lt;host&gt;[:&lt;port&gt;]/&lt;applicationComponent&gt;/&lt;apiName&gt;/&lt;apiVersion&gt;/&lt;resource&gt;/&lt;id&gt;</p>
  <p>Besides the Resource Identifier, CPI also supports:</p>
  <p>Field Restrictions</p>
  <p>HTTP Headers</p>
  <p>Resource Representation</p>
  <p>Query Patterns</p>
  <p>Task Patterns</p>
  <p>For more information about the Services supported by each
Interface, refer to Resources.</p>
  <body>
    <simpletable relcolwidth="1* 2*">
      <sthead>
        <stentry>Parameter</stentry>
        <stentry>Description</stentry>
      </sthead>
      <strow>
        <stentry>scheme</stentry>
        <stentry>The Application protocol, for example HTTP.</stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
        <stentry>host</stentry>
        <stentry>The network address to access the interface and its connected
service.</stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
        <stentry>port</stentry>
        <stentry>The TCP/IP port used for access. If not specified, default
ports for the applications are assumed.</stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
        <stentry>applicationComponent</stentry>
        <stentry>The name of the application component providing the resource.</stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
        <stentry>apiName</stentry>
        <stentry>The name of the interface.</stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
        <stentry>apiVersion</stentry>
        <stentry>The version mechanism is not used. The value is always v1</stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
        <stentry>resource</stentry>
        <stentry>The resource name.</stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
        <stentry>id</stentry>
        <stentry>The resource unique identifier.</stentry>
      </strow>
    </simpletable>
